{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Some bacteria, including Salmonella enterica subsp. enterica serovar Typhimurium, degrade 1,2-propanediol by a pathway that requires coenzyme B12, adenosylcobalamin (AdoCbl). Bacteria that harbour this pathway can use propanediol as a sole carbon and energy source. Proteins required for 1,2-propanediol degradation are encoded by the<i>pdu</i>operon [[cite:PUB00011184]]. Members of this family belong to the GHMP kinase domain superfamily (and are distantly related to galactokinase, L-homoserine kinase, and mevalonate kinase). Since cobalamin biosynthesis requires L-threonine-3P as a substrate for the CobD aminotransferase, PduX is cobalamin biosynthesis-related, which functions in the propanediol degradation pathway as L-threonine kinase [[cite:PUB00015657], [cite:PUB00101731]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR020568", "name" "Ribosomal protein uS5 domain 2-type superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF033887" "Predicted propanediol utilization/coumermycin biosynthesis protein, PduX type"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "L-threonine kinase", "short" "PduX"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 400, "taxa" 2215, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2269, "sets" 0, "proteins" 2267, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1834}, "pathways" 1}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommendations of the Nomenclature Committee of the International Union of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology (IUBMB) and it describes each type of characterized enzyme for which an EC (Enzyme Commission) number has been provided.", "rank" 19, "accessions" [{"